summary: ⚠️❗️Read at your own risk.❗️⚠️  Tony Stark is an example of resilience and courage. He is ready to sacrifice everything to the...
caption:
⚠️❗️Read at your own risk.❗️⚠️

Tony Stark is an example of resilience and courage.
He is ready to sacrifice everything to the people around him were alive and happy.
Endgame struck me to the depths of my soul, and I don’t know how soon I can move away from this, because my heart has finally broken.
Thank you, Tony, for all that you taught us.
Thanks to Robert for bringing such a wonderful character on the screen.

LOVE YOU 3000.  

Ok, since I decided to make an art blog out of it, this will be my first art here.

summary: why i am mad at marvel (if anyone still cares yes there are spoilers):
body:
why i am mad at marvel (if anyone still cares yes there are spoilers):

1. bucky didn’t get to find happiness by steve’s side. even if you view them as friends, not lovers, they still deserve to be happy together. no one will be able to support bucky as much as steve could.


2. steve took away peggy’s life she could’ve lived happily without him. for those who haven’t seen agent carter: they all mourned for cap, yes, but the main thing was to move on. to get over it and live a happy life without him. we even see peggy start a relationship that may very well be the one she got her kids and grandkids from. and yet marvel ruins all of that for what? for nothing. for some unknown reason they just make steve’s failed relationship into the “love of his life” she never was.


3. they make it seem like it was a good decision. like that was what made steve happy once and for all. like that was what he has been fighting for all these years. like he mourned for peggy more than he did for bucky. like she was more important to him. like doing that solved every problem.


in endgame they made steve rogers into a selfish man who leaves his best friend who needs him by his side more than anything to go ruin his almost-ex-girlfriend’s life, steve rogers as a character down the drain. i’m so fucking done.

summary: I remember The Avengers being my first major movie that I was seeing in a cinema
body:
I remember The Avengers being my first major movie that I was seeing in a cinema

I was 11, just getting into MARVEL movies, and was super excited to see The Avengers. To prepare, I watched Iron Man 1 and 2, Captain America and Thor just so I knew what was going on. It wasn’t until later that I saw The Incredible Hulk. I just remember that pure awe I felt watching these movies, the look of joy I must’ve had on my face while watching. I got so into them that I obsessed over the lore and the comics. When I saw The Avengers I’m not entirely sure I blinked once, but I was amazed. from that day on, this universe became a huge part of my life. I got into Agents of SHIELD, I was reading the comics, I was theorising and obsessing over my favourite characters, drawing them over and over.

I remember seeing Captain America 2 with my dad, and coming out thinking it was the best Marvel movie that had been released at that point. I remember when I went to see Guardians of the Galaxy and I was so in awe over everything. I remember when my dad bought me my first Pop! Vinyl, Rocket Racoon, just before seeing Big Hero Six and That started an obsession. Quickly after, I added Captain America and Star Lord to my collection. My dad bought me Marvel Collector Corps boxes as a surprise when they were made available to Australia, and soon I had way more Pop! Vinyls to count, and a box of Comics.

I remember crying in Iron Man 3, I remember being so excited for Quicksilver and Scarlet Witch to be involved, and crying when they killed off Quicksilver. I remember being excited to see Thor 2 and seeing Christopher Eccleston on screen again since Doctor Who, even if it was as the villain. I remember my Dad taking me to the Doctor Strange premier in 3D where they gave us a poster and a Pop! Vinyl at the door. I remember loving that movie the moment it started. I remember getting into Daredevil, and being so excited for one of my other favourite comic heroes coming to life. I got into Iron Fist, Jessica Jones and Luke Cage later, finding another form of happiness and release in street level heroes.

I remember Civil War and being incredibly excited at my favourite superhero, Spider-Man’s involvement. I remember not sure what side I’d be on, but ultimately being on Cap’s team. I remember GOTG2 and loving baby Groot and Rocket. I remember Homecoming and being so happy that Spider-Man was getting a proper MCU introduction and so impressed with Tom Holland’s portrayal that it quickly became my favourite. I remember not seeing Black Panther in theatres, but we bought it and while it wasn’t my favourite of the movies, it still held that MCU awe factor. I remember seeing Ant Man and laughing my head off. I remember seeing Infinity War and crying my eyes out. I remember seeing Ant Man 2 and loving it as well.

And most recently, I remember seeing Endgame, where I said goodbye to some of the most important and exciting parts of my life for the last ten years. I laughed, I cried, I got angry, then depressed. The one who started it all, Tony Stark, was dead and I wouldn’t be seeing another Iron Man appearance in the MCU again. Steve Rogers got all he wanted and lived a life. Natasha Romanoff, while getting a prequel movie, was gone. I said goodbye.

Thanks for 10 years of craziness and amazing characters.

We bid you farewell and a welcome to the newest iteration of Avengers; Black Panther, Spider-Man, Doctor Strange, Captain Marvel and more to come in the future.

We bid you farewell and a welcome to the newest iteration of Avengers; Black Panther, Spider-Man, Doctor Strange, Captain Marvel and more to come in the future.

summary:
someone give me the answers please 😭😭😭😭😭😭😭😭😭
Can someone tell me what to do next? Since Endgame is out and stuff... do we just...
body:
someone give me the answers please 😭😭😭😭😭😭😭😭😭

Can someone tell me what to do next? Since Endgame is out and stuff… do we just keep going? Are we never ever getting another Avengers movie ever again? And are we supposed to be ok with that? Or do we get Avengers 2.0 without the original six? And are we supposed to be ok with that? Or do we just keep making solo movies of the new/ other Marvel characters? And just accept that Endgame happened and that it was the ending of era?? And are we supposed to be ok with that??

WHAT DO I DO NOW???? I don’t know if I can keep going knowing (or rather not knowing) Chris Evans (RDJ, ScarJo & the rest of them too) won’t be in another Marvel movie ever again. Or that he’ll never play Captain America ever again. I don’t think I can live like this…. THIS SUCKS and I haven’t stopped crying since watching Endgame.

.

.

.

.

Maybe they can make a whole new Avengers series basically in a new parallel timeline where the previous plot didn’t happen???

Maybe we can keep going that way. After all that’s kind of how comic books work?

Who needs all the ends tied? Not me! Not us!

.

.

.

Or maybe the new Avengers (2.0 or whoever) can go back in time to the 40s and bring Steve back and back to 2019 and bring Natasha & Tony back!! And we can keep going that way!!!

.

.

.

Either way I REFUSE to accept this as the true ending to The Avengers. I want this to keep going. Whatever it takes.
